<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="285" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,423,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,423,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Head:</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[439,506,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[492,506,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) Head yellowish brown except ocellar triangle black; length: height: width ratio = 
<number box="[151,167,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[180,233,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.23">1.23</number>
: 
<number box="[243,295,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.35">1.35</number>
. Frons 
<number box="[377,457,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3-1.5</number>
times as wide as long. Frontal and orbital plates with yellowish setulae. Eye 
<number box="[1320,1369,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.65">1.65</number>
times as high as long. Antenna yellow, scape with 
<number box="[648,717,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
dark brownish setulae at dorso-apical margin; first flagellomere 
<number box="[151,200,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.45">1.45</number>
times as long as wide and distinctly rounded apicodorsally; arista very short pubescent, yellow at base and brown in its slender part. Gena 
<number box="[508,557,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="0.85">0.85</number>
times as high as first flagellomere and 
<number box="[1002,1051,296,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="0.33">0.33</number>
as high as eye. Proboscis capitate with yellowish brown setulae. Three frontal and two orbital setae present. All setae dark yellow and all setulae yellow except genal setulae anterior to genal seta short, brown. Palpus yellow, with sparse yellow and brown setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Thorax:</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[312,382,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[367,382,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) Yellow in ground color. Scutum 
<number box="[781,816,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times as wide as long (between presutural supra-alar setae). In greasy specimens small round black presutural spots are visible near supra-alar setae and black vitta is present in the middle of scutum from anterior margin, extending posteriorly beyond transverse suture. The black pattern is obscured by yellow microtrichia in dry specimens. Pleuron yellow; only triangular mark on katepisternum reddish brown, obscured by yellow microtrichia; scutellum subshining yellow; slightly wider than long, with 
<number box="[272,342,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15</number>
white setulae on each margin. Scutellum slightly convex with 
<number box="[1051,1065,584,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of setae (apical 
<number box="[1313,1348,584,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="0.9">0.9</number>
as long as basal one). Subscutellum and mediotergite yellow. All setae on thorax dark yellow. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,253,656,679]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Legs</emphasis>
: uniformly yellow, without modifications, not swollen; fore femur with 
<number box="[1073,1087,656,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of posterodorsal and one row of posteroventral setae; all setae and setulae yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Wing:</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[285,354,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[337,354,728,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hyaline with pattern of somewhat m-like appearance because of four well developed brownish crossbands. Base of wing, excluding (partly) distal half of cell c, cells bm and bcu and alula, yellowish brown. pterostigma entirely brown. Subbasal crossband reaching from pterostigma to vein A 
<number box="[1157,1165,814,828]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
+Cu 
<number box="[1213,1221,814,828]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
. Discal crossband complete, crossing wing from pterostigma through R-M crossvein, reaching posterior margin of the wing. Discal crossband fused with subbasal crossband in anterior margin (perostigma, cells r 
<number box="[1064,1072,889,903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
and r 
<number box="[1140,1148,889,903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1157,1164,889,903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
) of the wing. Preapical band complete, crossing wing from pterostigma through dm-cu crossvein, reaching posterior margin of the wing. Preapical and apical crossbands fused in cells r 
<number box="[674,682,964,978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
and r 
<number box="[744,752,964,978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[761,768,964,978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
; preapical and discal crossbands are converging and widely connected near posterior margin of wing, forming m-shape pattern. Brown spot present in the hyaline interspace between discal and preapical crossbands in cell r 
<number box="[715,723,1039,1053]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[741,809,1024,1049]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[796,809,1025,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<number box="[869,883,1025,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
<typeStatus box="[893,989,1025,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">paratype</typeStatus>
males this spot merged with preapical crossband (
<figureCitation box="[278,347,1063,1088]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,703,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,662,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Valera ariana, 1. Lateral habitus, Holotype, ♀. 2. Thorax. 3. Head in profile. 4. Wing, Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267647/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[330,347,1063,1087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Setae on dorsal side of vein R 
<number box="[700,708,1078,1092]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
without gap at Sc apex level. Vein R 
<number box="[1120,1128,1078,1092]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1137,1144,1078,1092]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="5.0">5</number>
with 
<number box="[1207,1249,1063,1088]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
setulae dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[199,318,1101,1126]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1101,1126]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Abdomen</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
General colour dark yellow; tergites without black spots, covered by white setulae; all setae yellow. Marginal setae on female tergites 
<number box="[527,569,1138,1163]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
pale yellow; tergite 
<number box="[796,810,1138,1163]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="5.0">5</number>
of male 
<number box="[907,942,1138,1162]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="0.3">0.3</number>
times as long as abdomen and without spots on hindmargin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[199,395,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,387,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Male terminalia</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Epandrium oval in dorsal view, with posterior lobe of lateral surstylus well protruding and moderately setulose. surstylus with two prensisetae. lateral prensiseta much smaller than medial one (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1349,1245,1270]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[1334,1349,1246,1270]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Glans of phallus as in 
<figureCitation box="[332,415,1282,1307]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[384,415,1282,1306]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
; with wide tubular base of acrophallus and rather large and wide apical semitubular lobes. Ejaculatory apodeme as in 
<figureCitation box="[454,522,1317,1342]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[505,522,1318,1342]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[199,423,1354,1379]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,413,1354,1379]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Female terminalia</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Oviscape brown, about as long as preabdomen. Aculeus brown, length/width ratio = 
<number box="[1387,1436,1354,1379]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="6.25">6.25</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1389,1414]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[211,227,1389,1414]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aculeus tip blunt with pair of preapical steps (
<figureCitation box="[764,831,1389,1414]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[815,831,1389,1414]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Two round densely and long papillose spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[159,228,1426,1451]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[250,1383,245,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[214,1404,196,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 10. Valera ariana, 5. Aculeus. 6. Aculeus apex. 7. Spermatheca. 8. Epandrium, posterior view. 9. Ejaculatory apodeme. 10. Glans of phallus, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267648/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,228,1426,1450]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,1461,1486]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Measurements</emphasis>
. Female. Body length 
<quantity box="[635,723,1462,1486]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="8.3">8.3 mm</quantity>
(including the oviscape), wing length 
<quantity box="[1163,1254,1461,1486]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
. Aculeus length 
<quantity box="[151,254,1498,1523]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="2.25">2.25 mm</quantity>
. Male. Body length 
<quantity box="[481,645,1498,1523]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.875" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.25" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="5.875" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="5.25">5.25—6.5 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[797,914,1498,1523]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.85" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="5.85" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.7">5.7–6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="285" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1533,1558]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after Aria Mountain, near Kashmar (Khorasan Razavi Province), where the 
<typeStatus box="[192,240,1571,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">type</typeStatus>
species was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
